{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb6caefb-736f-4947-99ad-d6a06e11e630","content":"No worries — the config is the same regardless. Add a `.vscode/mcp.json` to your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"${workspaceFolder}/src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`dotnet run`** builds and launches the project automatically.\n- `${workspaceFolder}` resolves to your VS Code workspace root.\n\nAfter adding the file, open the Copilot chat panel in agent mode (`@`), and it will discover the server's tools automatically. You can verify by clicking the **tools icon** (🔧) in the chat input area — your server's tools should be listed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c6e9e75a-82ae-49b6-b59a-93298a500776","outputTokens":238},"id":"1fe13acb-e7d8-432c-b081-f874b7feab96","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:48:29.377Z","parentId":"289e8e53-79d0-4937-ac43-4a12a3647a33"}
